claim.claim-text:
11. A recombinant microbe comprising a biosynthetic pathway for converting a carbon source to quinic acid, said biosynthetic pathway comprising:
(A) means for catalyzing the synthesis of 3-deoxy-D-arabino-heptulosonic acid-7-phosphate (DAHP) from phosphoenolpyruvate and erythrose-4-phosphate comprising a 3-deoxy-D-arabino-heptulosonic acid-7-phosphate (DAHP) synthase enzyme that is insensitive to feedback inhibition by aromatic amino acids encoded by an aroFFBR gene from E. coli; 
(B) means for catalyzing the synthesis of 3-dehydroquinate (DHQ) from DAHP comprising a 3-dehydroquinate (DHQ) synthase enzyme encoded by an aroB gene from E. coli; and
(C) means for catalyzing the synthesis of shikimic acid from 3-dehydroshikimic acid and for catalyzing the synthesis of quinic acid from DHQ comprising a shikimate dehydrogenase enzyme encoded by an aroE gene from E. coli; 
wherein at least one of the aroFFBR gene, the aroB gene, and the aroE gene is recombinant.
